it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface Individual.ObjectLink<O,J,Y extends Semantic.SemanticAxiom<S,?>,S,D extends ObjectProperty<O,S>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of ontology in which the axioms for classes will be applied.
    J - the type of the described individual.
    Y - the type of SemanticAxiom synchronised by this descriptor
    S - the type of semantic described by this class (i.e.: OWLObjectProperty)
    D - the type of the DataProperty descriptors instantiated during buildObjectIndividual() through #getNewObjectIndividual(SemanticAxiom, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Individual<O,J>, Semantic, Semantic.Descriptor<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MORIndividual.ObjectLink<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MORFullIndividual, MORLinkIndividual
    Enclosing interface:
    Individual<O,J>

    public static interface Individual.ObjectLink<O,J,Y extends Semantic.SemanticAxiom<S,?>,S,D extends ObjectProperty<O,S>>
extends Individual<O,J>
    The Semantic.Descriptor for the object properties applied to the described individuals.

    This Semantic.Descriptor synchronises only the specified object property and relative values for an ontological individual (i.e.: the Ground#getGroundInstance()).
    By default, the synchronisation occurs only for the proprieties which semantics have been initialised in the SemanticAxioms (getObjectSemantics()), not for all relations in the OWL representation. Anyway if the SemanticAxioms is leaved empty during readSemantic() it maps all the object properties applied to the described individual.

        default java.util.List<Semantic.MappingIntent> readSemantic()
        Description copied from interface: Semantic.Descriptor
        This method is used to synchronise specific Semantic.Axioms (or Semantic.SemanticAxioms) from the ontology. It manipulates the OWLLOOP representation to be equal to the queried OWL structure. It is based on Axioms#synchroniseFrom(Axioms).
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        the changes made in the Semantic.Axioms during the reading. Those objects may not have the Semantic.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).
